OL,6,F'It's like the day the Black Country
OL,7,Fdied'
OL,9,FThe loss of the Crooked House pub
OL,10,Fsparked an immediate outcry from
OL,11,Flocals and supporters nationwide.
OL,13,FKnown as a centrepiece of the
OL,14,Fcommunity and a tourist attraction,
OL,15,Fits destruction was felt deeply.
OL,17,FFlowers and cards of sympathy were
OL,18,Fleft at the site, and one local said:
OL,19,F"It's like the day the Black Country
OL,20,Fdied."
