OL,6,FSupporters argued that restoring the
OL,7,Fpub to its former glory was essential
OL,8,Ffor preserving the cultural and
OL,9,Fhistorical heritage of the area.
OL,11,FThe Save the Crooked House group,
OL,12,Fwhich has over 35,000 members, has
OL,13,Fbeen campaigning for the last six
OL,14,Fmonths since the historic 18th-century
OL,15,Fpub burned down.
OL,17,FPaul Turner, a campaigner from Save
OL,18,FThe Crooked House, said they need all
OL,19,Fthe support they can to get the pub
OL,20,Frebuilt
